Posted in Gitter chat:

@toddgibson 00:23
I'm not sure if I'm doing something wrong or it's a bug, but when working on a C# script on PC or Mac (Visual Studio 2015 CE, Xamarin Studio 6.x) if I make a change to the script in VS/XS and then go back and run the game from the AtomicEditor it doesn't see those script changes. Running it from either VS/XS works, but I'm not sure why they aren't syncing up. Is this known or am I missing a step?

@toddgibson 00:37
oh, I had to manually go into AtomicEditor menu and click Developer->Plugins->AtomicNet->Compile Project and then it synced up again... seems like it should watch those files and auto-compile or something.
Even with "Compile on Save" turned on I get the same result.
